<img class="aligncenter wp-image-1121939 lazyload" src="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/pastor-wins.jpeg" alt="" width="1280" height="666" srcset="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/pastor-wins.jpeg 696w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/pastor-wins-487x253.jpeg 487w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/pastor-wins-320x166.jpeg 320w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/pastor-wins-640x333.jpeg 640w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/pastor-wins-600x312.jpeg 600w" sizes="(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px" /> A Nigerian pastor has left his members shocked after he contested in a Guinness Drinking Competition. A pastor believed to be a preacher in Ibewe New Light Ministry Church became an internet sensation when the news of how he won a drinking competition set up by Guinness went viral. The congregations are in total shock when they discovered it was their pastor who won in such competition and more shocked at the fact that he participated in such competition. Also, many who know him are surprised that a man of his calibre and status would go-ahead to participate in a competition like that knowing full well a lot of people are looking up to him. From the competition, the pastor has won for himself a trip to Cairo and a brand new Toyota Camry.